---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About" description="Goutham Madhadi — data integrity practitioner and quality leader in cell and gene therapy biotech.">
  <div class="about">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="page-label">About</div>
      <h1>Goutham Madhadi</h1>
      <p class="tagline">Director of Digital Quality & Data Integrity · Cell & Gene Therapy</p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-body">
      <p>
        I lead data integrity and digital quality programs in the cell and gene therapy space —
        a domain where the data underpinning a single lot release can include millions of instrument
        records, dozens of novel assays, and scrutiny that extends all the way to BLA submission.
      </p>

      <p>
        This site exists because data integrity is frequently taught wrong: as a compliance exercise
        rather than as a fundamental property of good science. My goal here is to write about it
        the way practitioners actually experience it — not as a checklist, but as a discipline
        with real failure modes, real regulatory consequences, and real engineering solutions.
      </p>

      <h2>What I work on</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>FDA 21 CFR Part 11 compliance and audit trail integrity programs</li>
        <li>ALCOA+ data quality frameworks across GxP systems</li>
        <li>Computerized system validation (CSV) and change control</li>
        <li>BLA data packages and regulatory submission strategy</li>
        <li>AI-assisted tools for compliance monitoring and anomaly detection</li>
        <li>Data governance: roles, metadata standards, system interoperability</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        I've spent 15+ years across pharma and biotech building quality systems,
        leading inspections, and designing the data infrastructure that supports
        regulated manufacturing and clinical operations.
      </p>
      <p>
        Along the way I've sat in FDA inspection conference rooms, led data
        integrity remediation programs after findings, built LIMS and ELN validation
        packages from scratch, and watched companies both succeed and fail at
        building durable data quality cultures.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've also built most of the tools on this site myself — because the commercial
        options for GxP data intelligence are expensive, inflexible, and usually not
        designed by people who have actually run a GxP audit trail review.
      </p>

      <h2>Why cell & gene therapy</h2>
      <p>
        CGT sits at an unusual intersection: novel science, limited historical precedent,
        intense regulatory scrutiny, and an expectation of BLA-quality data from very
        early in development. The data integrity challenges are not just bigger — they're
        structurally different. That's what makes it worth writing about in depth.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Email me at <a href="mailto:goutham@madhadi.com">goutham@madhadi.com</a>.
        I'm open to conversations about data integrity programs, GxP system design,
        AI in regulated environments, or anything written on this site.
      </p>

      <div class="disclaimer">
        All opinions on this site are my own. Nothing here constitutes legal or regulatory advice.
        For specific compliance questions, consult a qualified regulatory affairs professional.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .page-label {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    color: var(--accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 { font-size: 2.25rem; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }

  .tagline {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-body {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .about-body p { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; color: #94a3b8; }

  .about-body h2 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 2.75rem 0 0.85rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-dim);
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .about-body ul {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: #94a3b8;
  }

  .about-body li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

  .about-body a {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .disclaimer {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--surface2);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
